2025-11-10: Bruno Lévy <Bruno.Levy@inria.fr>
	* mini-gmp.h (MINI_GMP_PLUS_BUFF_SIZE): only define
	MINI_GMP_PLUS_BUFF_SIZE if not already defined and if
	MINI_GMP_PLUS_NO_BUFF is not defined. Note: make sure you use the
	same MINI_GMP_PLUS_BUFF_SIZE when you compile mini-gmp-plus and when
	you compile a program that uses it !

2025-11-06: Bruno Lévy <Bruno.Levy@inria.fr>
        * t-add.c:
	* t-sub.c:
	* t-mul.c: Defined MAXBITS as 321 (5*64) in order to test
	operations combining numbers that fit in the local buffers with numbers
	that use dynamically allocated limbs

2025-11-04: Bruno Lévy <Bruno.Levy@inria.fr>
        * tests/CMakeLists.txt:
	* CMakeLists.txt:
        * .github/workflows/build.yml: CMakeLists and github action to build
	mini-gmp-plus and test it with mini-gmp testsuite under
	Mac/Linux/Windows. Use cmake -DMINI_GMP_PLUS_WITH_TESTS=1 to compile
	the tests. The tests need gmp. The github action installs it under
	Windows using vcpkg (and uses the already installed version in MacOS
	and Linux).
        * mini-gmp.h (gmp_lucas_mod): made this function public (used in tests)
        * bitops64.h: new file with operations for 64-bit integers, wrapping
	intrinsics for Linux/Mac/Windows
	* tests/testutils.c: linking with libmini-gmp-plus instead of #including
	mini-gmp.c and mini-mpq.c in tests/testutils.c directly, so that we
	can also test whether dynamic linking works.

2025-10-19: Bruno Lévy <Bruno.Levy@inria.fr>
	* mini-gmp.h:
	  - limb_t defined as uint64_t, from stdint.h
	  - MINI_GMP_PLUS_API import / export decl spec
	  - local buffer in mpz_t for avoiding dynamic allocation for small
	    numbers. MINI_GMP_PLUS_BUFF_SIZE defines the threshold (set to 5).
	* mini-gmp.c: taking into account MINI_GMP_PLUS_BUFF_SIZE
